properties.injury_desc: PROP STRIKE. DESTROYED 1st to THIRD COSTALS RHS.
properties.cod_cause_of_death_desc: COD most likely due to prop strike, considering no indications of ill health.

properties.fouling_epibionts_desc: Large barnacles on carapace, plastron, and soft tissue. Algae present on carapace.
properties.injury_desc: Injuries to neck consistent with ligature rubbing, damage to front flipper shoulder area, left front flipper large laceration looks more healed than other injuries, injury to end of front right flipper, cracks in carapace near tail area.
properties.alive_and_rescued_notes: Emaciated, damage to skin on neck, front left flipper laceration, small injury to right front flipper on the end, some barnacles, algae cover, sunken plastron. Some cracks / damage to back of carapace.

properties.fouling_epibionts_desc: 3 large barnacles left side of carapace
properties.abnormalities_desc: singular minor scute peeling, could have been from barnacle dislodgement.

properties.crab_pot_additional_info: NO INFORMATION ON CRAB POT AVAILABLE, NO PHOTOS AVAILABLE

properties.cause_of_stranding: Hooked/Entangled in Shark Control Program Drumline

properties.injury_desc: Minor cuts/scrapes from entanglement on both peduncle and fluke.
properties.cause_of_stranding: Hooked/entangled in fishing line or ingested fishing line
properties.alive_and_rescued_notes: Sea World caught animal, restrained for a 53 second disentanglement (from catch to release). Monofilament line around peduncle and fluke.
